Here's a minimal API endpoint that accepts multiple images plus a description field via `multipart/form-data`:

```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Http.Features;

var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

// Raise the max request body size to 50 MB
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o =>
    o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 50 * 1024 * 1024);

var app = builder.Build();

app.MapPost("/upload", async (
    IFormFileCollection files,   // bound from all file parts
    HttpRequest request) =>
{
    // Read the text field from the form
    var description = request.Form["description"].ToString();

    if (files.Count == 0)
        return Results.BadRequest("No files uploaded.");

    var saved = new List<string>();

    foreach (var file in files)
    {
        // Validate content type
        if (!file.ContentType.StartsWith("image/"))
            return Results.BadRequest($"'{file.FileName}' is not an image.");

        var path = Path.Combine("uploads", file.FileName);
        Directory.CreateDirectory("uploads");

        await using var stream = File.Create(path);
        await file.CopyToAsync(stream);
        saved.Add(file.FileName);
    }

    return Results.Ok(new { description, uploadedFiles = saved });
})
.DisableAntiforgery()   // required for minimal APIs accepting forms without a token
.Accepts<IFormFile>("multipart/form-data");

app.Run();
```

**Key points:**

- **`MaxRequestBodySize`** — Kestrel defaults to ~28 MB; set it to 50 MB explicitly.
- **`IFormFileCollection`** — binds every file part regardless of field name. Use `IFormFile` if you expect exactly one.
- **`request.Form["description"]`** — reads non-file form fields by name.
- **`.DisableAntiforgery()`** — without this, minimal APIs reject form POSTs that lack an antiforgery token (added by default in .NET 8).

**Example `curl` call:**

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/upload \
  -F "files=@photo1.jpg" \
  -F "files=@photo2.png" \
  -F "description=Vacation photos"
```

If you'd rather bind everything into a single typed model, replace the handler parameters with:

```csharp
app.MapPost("/upload", async ([AsParameters] UploadRequest req) => { ... });

public class UploadRequest
{
    public required IFormFileCollection Files { get; set; }

    [FromForm]
    public required string Description { get; set; }
}
```
